verbs.description: unplume (third-person singular simple present unplumes, present participle unpluming, simple past and past participle unplumed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To strip of plumes or feathers.
examples: "If I unplume and unjewel my cap," said the youth, tearing off, as he spoke, the feather and brooch that were its ornaments, and dashing them to the earth,  […]
